# Trivy/tfsec ignores for terraform-aws-secretsmanager. AVD-prefixed IDs
# (required when a resource is scanned through a module call) + justification.

# AVD-AWS-0098 — "Secret is not encrypted with a customer-managed key".
#
# The module supports a customer-managed key (module-level `kms_key_id` or a
# per-secret override) and the examples use one. When neither is supplied,
# Secrets Manager still encrypts at rest with the AWS-managed
# `aws/secretsmanager` key — a valid, zero-cost choice. We therefore make the
# CMK opt-in rather than forcing it, and suppress the scanner's blanket flag.
#
# Defined at: main.tf  resource "aws_secretsmanager_secret" "this"  (kms_key_id)
AVD-AWS-0098
